Articles
1. Complete the sentences with the articles a, the.
a) This is ___ house. ____ house is big and old. There is ___ playground near ___ house. ____
playground is not big but it is nice. There is ___ bench near ___ playground.
b) My friend and I went to ___ café yesterday. It is ___ small café not far from ___ theatre. We
had ____ nice meal there. We went to ___ café for ___ first time. We had ___ good time in ___
café.
2. Read the letter and fill the articles.
Hello, my friend!
My name is Nick. I am ___ youngest in my family. I have got ___ brother. His name is Mark.
He is ___ student, and I am ____ pupil. I study in ___ seventh form. My school is ____ best in
our town. I go to school five days ____ week. I have got ____ pet. It is ____ black puppy
called Rocky. We like to play together and on weekends we often go to ____ countryside when
the weather is good. My parents have got ____ house and small garden in ____ country. I like
to spend my weekends in ____ countryside.
Bye, Nick
3. Complete the sentences with the articles a/ the where necessary.
We have ___ big flat. Our ___ flat is on ___ fifth floor. There are ____ three rooms in ___ flat.
There is ____ large hall and ___ nice kitchen. ___ rooms are light and comfortable. I think my
____ bedroom is ____ best. There are two ___ windows in ___ bedroom. Our ___ house is not far
from my ____ school. I always walk to ___ school. My ___ lessons are over at ___ three o’clock,
so I come ____ home at four o’clock. We don’t go to ___ school on ____ Saturdays and Sundays.

Article the with Proper Names
1. Complete the sentences with the where necessary.
1) Do you know my friend ___ Mr Stevens? 2) ___ Edinburgh is ___ capital of ___
Scotland. 3) ___ Moores live in ____ Mill Street. 4) People of our country speaks
___ English and ___ Polish. 5) We have already visited ___ Metropolitan
Museum. 6) They often stay at ____ Devon Hotel when they visit ____
Liverpool. 7) My uncle prefers to spend his vacations in ___ Rocky Mountains.
2. Complete the sentences with the articles a or the where necessary.
___ Margaret Thatcher is ___ second daughter of ____ dressmaker, who became ____
first woman Prime Minister in ____ Europe. She was born on ____ October 13, 1925 in
____ England. She got her education at ____ Somerville College and at _____ Oxford
University. For some time she worked as ___ research chemist. ____ Margaret Thatcher
has become one of ___ most outstanding people in ___ history of ___ political life in
____ Britain.
3. Complete the sentences with the articles a or the where necessary.
___ Francis Drake, one of ___ most famous of ____ English sailors and pirates, was
born in ___ Plymouth, ___ largest town in the south of ____ England. ____ Francis was
____ twenty-five when he became ____ captain. In ___ November, 1577, ____ five
ships headed by Drake left ___ Plymouth and crossed ____ Atlantic Ocean. They sailed
along ____ American continent, crossed ____ Pacific Ocean and visited ____ Java
Island. Sailing north along the west coast of ____ Africa, Drake visited __ Canary
Islands and returned to ___ England in ____ September, 1580. He was ___ first ___
Englishman who sailed round ____ world.
